Certainly! Here's a thesis statement in LaTeX format for an article discussing the various manifestations of stress and coping strategies:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}

\textbf{Thesis Statement:} 
The multifaceted nature of stress manifests in physiological, psychological, and behavioral dimensions, necessitating a comprehensive exploration of coping strategies such as cognitive-behavioral techniques, mindfulness-based stress reduction, and social support systems to effectively mitigate its impact on individual well-being.

\end{document}
```

This thesis statement outlines the complexity of stress manifestations and highlights the importance of exploring various coping strategies to address the issue comprehensively.
